        "type": "TextualBody",
        "value": "The \"Create Page\" function doesn't have to be used as a space for contextual information. My role on the project, and as a contributor to a larger collaborative project, has informed my use of these pages. While I've found them to be most helpful for providing context, they may also be used as space for discussing different audio artifacts, providing images, or separate reference pages or biographies for associated authors. This flexibility is allows AVAnnotate to appeal to a wide variety of users, which makes it an essential tool across disciplines.",
